# Deployment Guide

## Local Development

### Mule Standalone Runtime
- Location: `softwares/mule-standalone/` (Mule EE 4.11.2)
- Start: `$MULE_HOME/bin/mule start`
- Stop: `$MULE_HOME/bin/mule stop`
- Apps dir: `$MULE_HOME/apps/` -- drop JAR files here for hot deploy
- Logs: `$MULE_HOME/logs/mule_ee.log`
- System property: `-Dmule.env=local` (set in `conf/wrapper.conf`)

### Building and Deploying Locally
```bash
cd projects/<api-name>
mvn clean package -DskipTests
cp target/<api-name>-*.jar $MULE_HOME/apps/
```

### Port Convention
| API | Port |
|-----|------|
| customer-papi | 8081 |
| customer-management-api | 8082 |
| customer-sf-sapi | 8083 |
| customer-mock-service | 8084 |

## CloudHub 2.0 Deployment

### Prerequisites
- Connected App credentials in Maven `settings.xml` (server ID: `anypoint-exchange-v3`)
- Org ID as groupId in pom.xml

### Publish to Exchange
```bash
mvn clean deploy -DskipTests
```

### Deploy to CloudHub
```bash
mvn clean package mule:deploy -DskipTests -Pcloudhub2 \
  -Dch2.clientId=<CLIENT_ID> \
  -Dch2.clientSecret=<CLIENT_SECRET> \
  -Dch2.environment=Sandbox \
  -Dch2.target=Cloudhub-US-East-2 \
  "-Dch2.muleVersion=4.11.2:3e-java17" \
  -Dch2.applicationName=<prefix>-<api-name> \
  -Dch2.replicas=1 \
  -Dch2.vCores=0.1
```

### CloudHub App Naming
Uses `{org.cloudhub_prefix}` from config.yaml as prefix:
- `{prefix}-customer-papi`
- `{prefix}-customer-mgmt-api`
- `{prefix}-customer-sf-sapi`

### Important Notes
- Always set `mule.env=cloudhub` in the CloudHub deployment properties block
- Runtime version must match what's available on the target (check via Anypoint API)
- Asset must be published to Exchange before first CloudHub deploy
- Subsequent deploys can use `mule:deploy` directly (skip Exchange re-publish)
